The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bhutia: We want to be consistent

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: A new season and a new role. For Bhaichung Bhutia, who has been named Mohun Bagan captain for the forthcoming season, the immediate target would be to get the team to perform as an unit. 

Leading a club officially for the first time, Bhutia says: Its great honour for me Officially, Ill be leading a club for the first time, as I did captain East Bengal for a few matches in the past. 

The nippy striker, who has turned out for local giants East Bengal and Mohun Bagan besides JCT and also English second division side Bury FC and Penang FC of Malaysia, said: The immediate target is to combine together as an unit The goal however is to perform better than last year. 

About the composition of the squad, he said: Weve very good players. Its almost similar to that of last time. However injury took a toll on most of our players as we were quite inconsistent last season. We want to be consistent this time. 

Welcoming the clubs decision to appoint Carlos Pereira as coach, he said: Ive not played under him, but Ive heard other players showering praises on the Brazilians technical brilliance. 




